DTSTART:20260621T233000Z
DTEND:20260622T013000Z
SUMMARY:Southern Avenue at Jimmy's Jazz & Blues Club
LOCATION:135 Congress St\, Portsmouth\, NH 03801
DESCRIPTION:Memphis-based blues\, soul and gospel-flavored roots band front
 ed by vocalist Tierinii Jackson and guitarist Ori Naftaly. Their 2025 Alli
 gator Records debut Family earned a Best Contemporary Blues Album nominati
 on at the 2026 Grammys\, their second Grammy nod after 2019's Keep On. Tic
 kets: https://jimmysoncongress.com/event/southern-avenue/
CATEGORIES:blues
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-21-joe-hunt-jazz-quintet-2a443250@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260622T003000Z
DTEND:20260622T023000Z
SUMMARY:Joe Hunt Jazz Quintet at Jazz Boston Calendar
LOCATION:The Lilypad\, Cambridge
DESCRIPTION:Joe Hunt (b. 1938) is a low-key Boston jazz legend\, a drummer 
 who recorded with the George Russell Sextet\, the Stan Getz Quartet (1964-
 65\, on Verve) and the Bill Evans Trio (1966-67)\, then taught at Berklee'
 s jazz program for 31 years. Tickets: https://jazzboston.org/jazz-calendar
 ?joe-hunt-jazz-quintet&event_id=425467&fid=1
CATEGORIES:jazz
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-22-local-artist-series-the-knickerbocker-all-stars-567adb38@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260622T230000Z
DTEND:20260623T010000Z
SUMMARY:Local Artist Series: The Knickerbocker All-Stars at Jimmy's Jazz & 
 Blues Club
LOCATION:135 Congress St\, Portsmouth\, NH 03801
DESCRIPTION:The Knickerbocker All-Stars are a 9-piece New England blues\, j
 ump blues\, R&B and soul revue named for the historic Knickerbocker Café 
 in Westerly\, RI\, drawing on Roomful of Blues alumni and other top region
 al players. They earned a Blues Music Award nomination for Best Soul Blues
  Album (2018) and reached #1 on the Living Blues radio chart. Tickets: htt
 ps://jimmysoncongress.com/event/local-artist-series-the-knickerbocker-all-
 stars/
CATEGORIES:blues
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-24-eli-block-quintet-4e9b1218@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260624T230000Z
DTEND:20260625T010000Z
SUMMARY:Eli Block Quintet at Jazz Boston Calendar
LOCATION:The Mad Monkfish\, Cambridge
DESCRIPTION:Eli Block is a Boston-based jazz trumpet player\, composer and 
 educator who leads the Eli Block Quintet. He earned a Master's in Jazz Per
 formance with honors from New England Conservatory (2020)\, serves on NEC'
 s Expanded Education faculty\, and has performed with artists including Da
 ve Holland\, Dave Douglas\, Miguel Zenon and Antonio Sanchez. Tickets: htt
 ps://jazzboston.org/jazz-calendar?eli-block-quintet&event_id=424260&fid=1
CATEGORIES:jazz
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-25-fringe-1047aff2@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260625T220000Z
DTEND:20260626T000000Z
SUMMARY:The Fringe at Jazz Boston Calendar
LOCATION:Long Live Roxbury\, Boston
DESCRIPTION:The Fringe is a veteran Boston free-jazz trio formed in 1972 by
  tenor saxophonist George Garzone\, with bassist John Lockwood (since 1985
 ) and drummer Bob Gullotti (until his death in 2020)\, long known for thei
 r famed weekly Monday-night gigs and over 50 years as a Boston jazz instit
 ution. Tickets: https://jazzboston.org/jazz-calendar?the-fringe&event_id=4
 24530&fid=1
CATEGORIES:jazz
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-25-fabiola-mendez-william-cumpiano-d83f9a16@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260625T230000Z
DTEND:20260626T010000Z
SUMMARY:Fabiola Mendez & William Cumpiano at Jazz Boston Calendar
LOCATION:Concord Conservatory of Music\, Concord
DESCRIPTION:Fabiola Mendez is a Puerto Rican cuatro player\, singer\, educa
 tor\, and Emmy-nominated composer from Caguas\, PR. In 2018 she became the
  first Berklee graduate to play the Puerto Rican cuatro as principal instr
 ument. She blends folk\, Afro-Caribbean\, jazz\, and Latin music\, compose
 s for PBS Kids' 'Alma's Way\,' and was named Boston Music Awards Latin Art
 ist of the Year (2023). Tickets: https://jazzboston.org/jazz-calendar?fabi
 ola-mendez-william-cumpiano&event_id=424879&fid=1
CATEGORIES:jazz
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e-2026-06-25-taylor-eigsti-ac36b2f1@jazz-weekly.bitdoktor.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260619T020521Z
DTSTART:20260625T230000Z
DTEND:20260626T010000Z
SUMMARY:Taylor Eigsti at Regattabar
LOCATION:1 Bennett St\, Cambridge\, MA 02138
DESCRIPTION:Two-time Grammy-winning jazz pianist and composer\, a former pr
 odigy from Menlo Park who has released nine albums as a leader and appeare
 d on over 80 as a sideman. He won Best Contemporary Instrumental Album for
  Tree Falls (2022) and Plot Armor (2025)\, and tours with the likes of Jul
 ian Lage and Chris Botti. Tickets: https://www.ticketweb.com/venue/regatta
 bar-cambridge-ma/748814
CATEGORIES:jazz
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
